Martin BUTCHKO, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. CENTRAL RAILROAD COMPANY OF NEW JERSEY, Defendant-Appellant. No. 59. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. Nov. 1, 1937. Charles E. Miller, of New York City (William A. Dempsey and John J. Mc-Elhinny, both of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. Stephen A. Machcinski, of New York City (Morton L. Fearey and Wm. Paul Allen, both of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before L. HAND, AUGUSTUS N. HAND, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Judgment affirmed.
